cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for node embedding using linear models instead of graph convolutional networks (GCN) in graph autoencoders (AE) and variational autoencoders (VAE). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with developing new methods for learning representations of nodes in graphs. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on link prediction and node clustering tasks, which are common in the field of social network analysis (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach for real-world applications, which is relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
